I, too, have often thought that there should be a news channel devoted to good news only or that at least the existing news media should devote at least one day a week to only good and uplifting stories. Thank you for taking the time, not only to look, but for sharing what you found with us!

snippet.textDisplay:
Don't forget those still working in essential work aren't all doctors and nurses, they are the people that help you get your computer on so you can work at home, the guy that fixes your cable tv so you can watch the news, the welders who are building the frames for the pop up hospitals and so many more.. clap for all of them too !
I am one of those people in an essential business. I never thought tech support would be so essential? I've helped a least 50 people a day since the pandemic started get online so they can work from home or get their child online for school work. As we are all so stressed out not all our clients have been very nice, some are out right mean; but I totally understand. At the end of the day I have a good cry.. then deal with my own family and trying to find things we need that everyone who is off from work has already been able to get. I'm still trying to find hand sanitizer, lol.
Grateful and blessed to live in a nation of survivors, we don't have muscles you can see, we have big HEARTs and that's all we need ! I pray we don't get covid 19.

I needed this.. more than you know ! Thank you John !!
#alonetogether
